Subject:	CardConnect One - Call Process

Rod,

See below notes from Steve Sommers that were sent to me. I fully support the conference call process.

I understand the need for a CardConnect One process different than what we currently do for other gateways.

I have stated on numerous calls/meetings that the existing gateway process creates a great deal of extra work for CardConnect conversions. The current
gateway process forces us to touch the merchant twice.

I have no issue with CardConnect doing the conference calls(preferred method by me). I simply request the following:
    •   CardConnect must have properly skilled and trained tech support personal participate and lead the calls. I cannot continue to have my TSMs
         constantly complaining about how bad the CardConnect resources are on these calls. If my TSMs are going to participate in the calls, then
         CardConnect must provide a minimum Level 2 Support resource to lead the process.
    •   We all realize that these calls, at times, require lengthy troubleshooting which is fine assuming we are using this process to mitigate dual
         touches to the merchant and we have skilled resources working to resolution.
    •   CardConnect should provide a daily report recapping the number of attempted calls, completed calls and issues.

I am confident the number of cases opened would be reduced if we improved the conference call communication, process and expectations.

Please let me know if you have any questions.
Thank you
Randy
